<!-- -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=- -->
<sect1 id="ok" xreflabel="Ok Button">
<title>Ok Button</title>

<graphic format=GIF fileref="ok.gif"></graphic>

<para>
Click this button to apply all the changes you have made to this
dialog window and close the window.
</para>

<para>
See also:
<xref linkend="apply">
<xref linkend="cancel">
</para>

<para>
<xref linkend="index">
</para>

</sect1>

<!-- -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=- -->
<sect1 id="apply" xreflabel="Apply Button">
<title>Apply Button</title>

<graphic format=GIF fileref="apply.gif"></graphic>

<para>
Click this button to apply all the changes you have made to this
dialog window, without closing the dialog window.
</para>

<para>
See also:
<xref linkend="ok">
<xref linkend="cancel">
</para>

<para>
<xref linkend="index">
</para>

</sect1>

<!-- -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=- -->
<sect1 id="cancel" xreflabel="Cancel Button">
<title>Cancel Button</title>

<graphic format=GIF fileref="cancel.gif"></graphic>

<para>
Click this button to discard all the changes you have made to this
dialog window and close the dialog.
</para>

<para>
See also:
<xref linkend="ok">
<xref linkend="apply">
</para>

<para>
<xref linkend="index">
</para>

</sect1>

<!-- -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=- -->
<sect1 id="tools-again" xreflabel="Again tool">
<title>Again tool</title>

<graphic format=GIF fileref="tools-again.gif"></graphic>

<para>
Click this toolbar button to repeat the last <command>gmake</command> run,
i.e. run <command>gmake</command> with the same target you used last time
you ran <command>gmake</command>.  Look at the tooltip to see which
target will be built.
</para>

<para>
This toolbar button becomes available once you have done at least
one <command>gmake</command> run.
</para>

<para>
See also:
<xref linkend="tools-all">
<xref linkend="tools-clean">
<!-- <xref linkend="menu-build"> -->
</para>

<para>
<xref linkend="index">
</para>

</sect1>

<!-- -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=- -->
<sect1 id="tools-stop" xreflabel="Stop tool">
<title>Stop tool</title>

<graphic format=GIF fileref="tools-stop.gif"></graphic>

<para>
Click this toolbar button to stop the current <command>gmake</command> run.
</para>

<para>
This toolbar button becomes available only during a <command>gmake</command>
run.
</para>

<para>
See also:
<xref linkend="tools-all">
<xref linkend="tools-clean">
<!-- <xref linkend="menu-build"> -->
</para>

<para>
<xref linkend="index">
</para>

</sect1>

<!-- -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=- -->
<sect1 id="tools-all" xreflabel="Build All tool">
<title>Build All tool</title>

<graphic format=GIF fileref="tools-all.gif"></graphic>

<para>
Click this toolbar button to run <command>gmake</command> with the
target <varname>all</varname>.  Makefiles which adhere to GNU
Makefile standards define this target thus:
</para>

<blockquote>
  <para>
    Compile the entire program.  This should be the default target.
    This target need not rebuild any documentation files.
  </para>
</blockquote>

<para>
This toolbar button becomes available if the <filename>Makefile</filename>
in the current directory defines an <varname>all</varname> target, and
remains available while <command>gmake</command> is not running.
</para>

<para>
See also:
<xref linkend="tools-clean">
</para>

<para>
<xref linkend="index">
</para>

</sect1>

<!-- -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=- -->
<sect1 id="tools-clean" xreflabel="Build Clean tool">
<title>Build Clean tool</title>

<graphic format=GIF fileref="tools-clean.gif"></graphic>

<para>
Click this toolbar button to run <command>gmake</command> with the
target <varname>clean</varname>.  Makefiles which adhere to GNU
Makefile standards define this target thus:
</para>

<blockquote>
  <para>
    Delete all files from the current directory that are normally
    created by building the program.  Don't delete the files that
    record the configuration.  Also preserve files that could be
    made by building, but normally aren't because the distribution
    comes with them.
  </para>
</blockquote>

<para>
This toolbar button becomes available if the <filename>Makefile</filename>
in the current directory defines a <varname>clean</varname> target, and
remains available while <command>gmake</command> is not running.
</para>

<para>
See also:
<xref linkend="tools-all">
</para>

<para>
<xref linkend="index">
</para>

</sect1>

<!-- -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=- -->
<sect1 id="tools-clear" xreflabel="Clear Log tool">
<title>Clear Log tool</title>

<graphic format=GIF fileref="tools-clear.gif"></graphic>

<para>
Click this toolbar button to clear the log window, i.e. delete
all text in the window.
</para>

<para>
This toolbar button becomes available when the log window contains text.
</para>

<para>
<xref linkend="index">
</para>

</sect1>

<!-- -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=- -->
<sect1 id="tools-edit-next" xreflabel="Edit Next Error tool">
<title>Edit Next Error tool</title>

<graphic format=GIF fileref="tools-edit-next.gif"></graphic>

<para>
  Click this toolbar button to edit the next error or warning after the
  currently selected line in the log window.  If the <guilabel>Edit Next
  ignores warnings</guilabel> toggle in the <guilabel>Preferences</guilabel>
  window is set, this button will skip over warnings and only find errors.
</para>

<para>
  This toolbar button becomes available when the log window contains text.
</para>

<para>
  See also:
  <xref linkend="tools-edit-file-next">
</para>

<para>
  <xref linkend="index">
</para>

</sect1>

<!-- -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=- -->
<sect1 id="tools-edit-file-next" xreflabel="Edit File Next Error tool">
<title>Edit File Next Error tool</title>

<graphic format=GIF fileref="tools-edit-file-next.gif"></graphic>

<para>
  Click this toolbar button to edit the next error or warning after the
  currently selected line in the log window.  Unlike the
  <xref linkend="tools-edit-next">, this button first skips all errors
  and warnings in the same file as the selected line; this is useful
  when
  
  If the <guilabel>Edit Next
  ignores warnings</guilabel> toggle in the <guilabel>Preferences</guilabel>
  window is set, this button will skip over warnings and only find errors.
</para>

<para>
  This toolbar button becomes available when the log window contains text.
</para>

<para>
  See also:
  <xref linkend="tools-edit-next">
</para>

<para>
  <xref linkend="index">
</para>

</sect1>

<!-- -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=- -->
<sect1 id="tools-print" xreflabel="Print tool">
<title>Print tool</title>

<graphic format=GIF fileref="tools-print.gif"></graphic>

<para>
Click this toolbar button to repeat the last make run, i.e. run
<command>gmake</command> with the same target you used last time
you ran <command>gmake</command>.  Look at the tooltip to see which
target will be built.
</para>

<para>
This toolbar button becomes available once you have done at least
one <command>gmake</command> run.
</para>

<para>
See also:
<xref linkend="tools-all">
<xref linkend="tools-clean">
<!-- <xref linkend="menu-build"> -->
</para>

<para>
<xref linkend="index">
</para>

</sect1>

<!-- -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=- -->
<sect1 id="prefs-kflag" xreflabel="Continue despite failures">
<title>Continue despite failures</title>

<para>
Select this toggle to have <command>gmake</command> continue building
targets after a target fails to be built.  The normal behaviour of
<command>gmake</command> is to stop when the first target fails.
</para>

<para>
This toggle sets the <option>-k</option> flag to <command>gmake</command>.
</para>

<para>
<xref linkend="index">
</para>

</sect1>

